just_use apply_labels.py

# label: VESTIGIAL (label-triage bulk tool)
# role: one-shot — bulk-write `# label:` comments into .claude sidecars

Bulk writes per-file DX labels (WORKHORSE, ELEGANT, INTRICATE,
etc.) into `.claude` sidecars across the repo, and emits a
top-level `LABELS.md` index. Idempotent. Re-run when labels
change.

## Status (TENTATIVE)

The label assignments in this file are Claude's gut reactions
from the 2026-04-14 triage pass. As sidecars have been
hand-authored at the raised-bar since, this tool may be of
diminishing value — it overwrites the `# label:` comment in
each `.claude` but leaves body content alone, so it's safe to
re-run if you want consistent labels across a newly-added
batch. It does NOT know about labels invented after 2026-04-14
(SPIKE, EARLY, BUGGY, VESTIGIAL tiers all postdate this file).

If you're here looking for the authoritative label for a given
file, read the file's `.claude` directly — this script is not
the source of truth.

## Surface

- `python3 tools/apply_labels.py` — rewrites labels per the
  hardcoded `LABELS` map at the top, regenerates
  `LABELS.md`.
- The `LABELS` dict at the top of the file IS the label
  assignment map for the snapshot. Edit there, re-run.

## What it does NOT do

- Validate that a labeled file still exists.
- Compute labels from code metrics.
- Respect any label tiers added after 2026-04-14.

## Pointers

- Generated artifact: `LABELS.md` at repo root.
- Label-tier evolution: see memories
  `feedback_spike_label_new_features.md`,
  `feedback_early_label_tier.md`, `feedback_buggy_label.md`.
